kers (indoor)\n}}\n\nThe '''1980 [[Fort Lauderdale Strikers (1977\u201383)|Fort Lauderdale Strikers]] season''' was the fourth season of the Fort Lauderdale Striker's team, and the club's fourteenth season in professional soccer.  This year the team made it to the finals of [[North American Soccer League (1968\u201384)|North American Soccer League]] by reaching the [[Soccer Bowl '80|Soccer Bowl]].  They were this year's Runners-up.\n\n== Background ==\n{{Empty section|date=November 2013}}\n\n== Review ==\n{{Empty section|date=November 2013}}\n\n== Competitions ==\n=== Friendlies ===\nFort Lauderdale finished their preseason exhibition schedule with one victory over an [[NCAA Division II]] squad, and two draws versus [[Peruvian Primera Divisi\u00f3n|Peruvian First Division]] teams, three losses against NASL clubs and one loss to an [[NCAA Division II]] team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/234325233/?terms=Strikers%2Bpreseason|title=Strikers to begin 6 game exhibition season against Florida International|date=February 17, 1980|work=Fort Lauderdale News|page=6C|accessdate=18 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/234895315/?terms=Strikers%2Bexhibition|title=Strikers tie last exhibition|date=March 25, 1980|work=Fort Lauderdale News|page=6E|accessdate=18 September 2017}}</ref> In April after the NASL season had begun, the Strikers easily handled the [[Miami Hurricanes]] and the junior side, [[Calry Bohemian FC]], of [[Sligo]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Smith|first=Mike|url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/301850350/?terms=Strikers|title=The U-M athletic team nobody knows|date=April 15, 1980|work=Miami News|page=1C|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Wieczorek|first=Dave|url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/234942061/?terms=Strikers|title=Dutchman Pot prefers Strikers guard duty|date=April 17, 1980|work=Fort Lauderdale News|page=3D|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref> They later fell to visiting [[Sunderland A.F.C.]] in a midseason friendly in May.\n\n==== Results summaries ====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%; text-align:center\"\n!Date!!Opponent!!Venue!!Result!!Attendance!!Scorers\n|- bgcolor=\"#ffdddd\"\n|{{left}}March 2, 1980\n|{{left}}[[FIU Panthers men's soccer|FIU Sunblazers]]\n|[[Florida International University|FIU South Campus]]\n|2\u20133\n|\n|<small>???, ???</small>\n|-\n|- bgcolor=\"ddffdd\"\n|{{left}}March 9, 1980\n|{{left}}[[Miami Dade College|Miami Dade North Falcons]]\n|[[MDC North Campus|Dade North Stadium]]\n|8\u20130\n| \n|<small>M\u00fcller (3), Bonvallet (3), Cubillas, Cacciatore </small>\n|-\n|- bgcolor=\"ffdddd\"\n|{{left}}March 12, 1980\n|{{left}}[[Detroit Express]]\n|[[John I. Leonard Community High School|Leonard High School]]\n|0\u20131\n|\n|\n|-\n|- bgcolor=\"ffdddd\"\n|{{left}}March 16, 1980\n|{{left}}[[Detroit Express]]\n|[[Bryant Stadium]]\n|1\u20132''<small>(SO)</small>''\n|\n|<small>Nico Bodonczy</small>\n|-\n|- bgcolor=\"ffdddd\"\n|{{left}}March 19, 1980\n|{{left}}[[Minnesota Kicks]]\n|[[Coral Springs High School]]\n|0\u20131\n|\n|\n|-\n|- bgcolor= \n|{{left}}March 21, 1980\n|{{left}}[[Atlanta Chiefs]]\n|[[Lockhart Stadium]]\n| '''\u2013'''\n| '''\u2013'''\n|'''MATCH CANCELED'''\n|-\n|- bgcolor= \"ffebad\"\n|{{left}}March 22, 1980\n|{{left}}{{flagicon|PER}} [[Alianza Lima]]\n|[[Estadio Alejandro Villanueva|Estadio Alianza]]\n|1\u20131\n|35,000\n|<small> David Irving </small>\n|-\n|- bgcolor= \"ffebad\"\n|{{left}}March 24, 1980\n|{{left}}{{flagicon|PER}} [[Club Universitario de Deportes|Club Universitario]]\n|[[Estadio Alejandro Villanueva|Estadio Alianza]]\n|1\u20131\n|35,000\n|<small> Gerd M\u00fcller </small>\n|- bgcolor=\"ddffdd\"\n|{{left}}April 14, 1980\n|{{left}}[[Miami Hurricanes]]\n|[[Mark Light Stadium]]\n|6\u20131\n| \n|<small>David Irving </small>\n|- bgcolor=\"ddffdd\"\n|{{left}}April 16, 1980\n|{{left}}{{flagicon|IRE}} [[Calry Bohemian FC]]\n|Strikers practice facility\n|8\u20130\n| \n|<small>David Irving (3), Nico Bodonczy (2), Mike Ortiz-Velez (2)</small>\n|-\n|- bgcolor=\"ffdddd\"\n|{{left}}May 14, 1980\n|{{left}}{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Sunderland A.F.C.]]\n|[[Lockhart Stadium]]\n|1\u20132\n| 4,649<ref>https://www.newspapers.com/image/134924661/?terms=Sunderland</ref>\n|<small>Ray Hudson (pk)</small>\n|-\n|}\n\n=== NASL regular season ===\n\n==== Results summaries ====\n{{Empty section|date=November 2013}}\n\n==== Results by round ====\n{{Empty section|date=November 2013}}\n\n==== Match reports ====\n{{Empty section|date=November 2013}}\n\n=== NASL Playoffs ===\n\n'''Playoffs'''\n''In 1979 and 1980, if a playoff series was tied at one victory each, a full 30 minute mini-game was played. If neither team held an advantage after the 30 minutes, the teams would then move on to a shoot-out to determine a series winner.''<ref>https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=0rg0AAAAIBAJ&sjid=B24FAAAAIBAJ&pg=4566,2362302&dq=nasl+record+shootout&hl=en</ref>{{-}}\n\n==== First round====\n{| style=border-collapse:collapse border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=2\n|- align=center bgcolor=#efefef\n!width=180|Lower seed\n!width=5|\n!width=180|Higher seed\n!width=80|Game 1\n!width=80|Game 2\n!width=100|Mini-game\n|width=260|\n|- align=center bgcolor=fffafa\n|align=right|[[California Surf]]|| - ||align=left|'''Fort Lauderdale Strikers'''|| 1\u20132 || 2\u20130 || 0\u20131 <small>''(SO, 2\u20133)''</small> || <small>August 28 \u2022 [[Anaheim Stadium]] \u2022 2,929<br>August 31 \u2022 [[Lockhart Stadium]] \u2022 15,282</small>\n|}{{-}}\n\n====Conference Semifinals====\n{| style=border-collapse:collapse border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=2\n|- align=center bgcolor=#efefef\n!width=180|Lower seed\n!width=5|\n!width=180|Higher seed\n!width=80|Game 1\n!width=80|Game 2\n!width=100|Mini-game\n|width=260|\n|- align=center bgcolor=fffafa\n|align=right|[[Edmonton Drillers (1979\u201382)|Edmonton Drillers]]|| - ||align=left|'''Fort Lauderdale Strikers'''|| 0\u20131 || 3\u20132 <sma