mber 2013}}\n\n== Transfers ==\n{{Empty section|date=November 2013}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Fort Lauderdale Strikers}}\n{{North American Soccer League (1966\u201385)}}\n{{1980 in American soccer}}\n\n[[Category:Fort Lauderdale Strikers (1977\u20131983) seasons|1980]]\n[[Category:American soccer clubs 1980 season|Fort Lauderdale Strikers]]\n[[Category:1980 in sports in Florida|Fort Lauderdale Strikers]]\n[[Category:1980 North American Soccer League season|Fort Lauderdale]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football club season\n| club               = [[Fort Lauderdale Strikers (1977\u201383)|Fort Lauderdale Strikers]]\n| season             = [[1980 North American Soccer League season|1980]]\n| manager            = {{flagicon|Netherlands}} [[Cor van der Hart]]\n| owner               = {{flagicon|USA}} Elizabeth Robbie\n| chairman           = {{flagicon|CAN}} [[Bob Lemieux]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Suarez |first=Leo |title=Robbie relieving Lemieux, Strikers winning manager |date=October 15, 1980|newspaper=Miami News|url= https://www.newspapers.com/image/302351891/?terms=Strikers |page=3B|accessdate=July 27, 2017}}</ref> <small>''(fired Oct. 14)''</small><br>{{flagicon|USA}} Tim Robbie\n| chrtitle           = General Manager \n| stadium            = [[Lockhart Stadium]]\n| league             = [[North American Soccer League|NASL]]\n| league result      = '''Division''':Second Place<br />'''[[Soccer Bowl|NASL Championship]]:''' Finalist\n| cup1               = \n| cup1 result        = \n| league topscorer   = <br>{{flagicon|PER}} [[Te\u00f3filo Cubillas]] <br>{{flagicon|GER}} [[Gerd M\u00fcller]] <br><small> (14 goals) </small>\n| season topscorer   = <br>{{flagicon|PER}} [[Te\u00f3filo Cubillas]] <br><small> (18 goals) </small>\n| average attendance = 14,360\n| American           = True\n| pattern_la1=_red_hoops\n|pattern_b1=_Fort12Home\n|pattern_ra1=_red_hoops\n|pattern_sh1=_udeg1718h\n|pattern_so1=_redstripe\n|leftarm1=FFCC00\n|body1= FFCC00\n|rightarm1=FFCC00\n|shorts1=000000\n|socks1=000000\n|pattern_la2=_redborder\n|pattern_b2=_horizontalonwhite\n|pattern_ra2=_redborder\n|pattern_sh2=_redbottom\n|pattern_so2=_redstripe\n|leftarm2=FFFFFF\n|body2=FFFF99\n|rightarm2=FFFFFF\n|shorts2=FFFFFF\n|socks2=FFFFFF\n| prevseason = [[1979\u201380 Fort Lauderdale Strikers indoor season|1979\u201380]] Strikers (indoor)\n| nextseason = [[1980\u201381 Fort Lauderdale Strikers indoor season|1980\u201381]] Strikers (indoor)\n}}\n\nThe '''1980 [[Fort Lauderdale Strikers (1977\u201383)|Fort Lauderdale Strikers]] season''' was the fourth season of the Fort Lauderdale Striker's team, and the club's fourteenth season in professional soccer.  This year the team made it to the finals of [[North American Soccer League (1968\u201384)|North American Soccer League]] by reaching the [[Soccer Bowl '80|Soccer Bowl]].  They were this year's Runners-up.\n\n== Background ==\n{{Empty section|date=November 2013}}\n\n== Review ==\n{{Empty section|date=November 2013}}\n\n== Competitions ==\n=== Friendlies ===\nFort Lauderdale finished their preseason exhibition schedule with one victory over an [[NCAA Division II]] squad, and two draw versus [[Peruvian Primera Divisi\u00f3n|Peruvian First Division]] teams three losses against NASL clubs and one loss to an [[NCAA Division II]] team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/234325233/?terms=Strikers%2Bpreseason|title=Strikers to begin 6 game exhibition season against Florida International|date=February 17, 1980|work=Fort Lauderdale News|page=6C|accessdate=18 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/234895315/?terms=Strikers%2Bexhibition|title=Strikers tie last exhibition|date=March 25, 1980|work=Fort Lauderdale News|page=6E|accessdate=18 September 2017}}</ref> In April after the NASL season had begun, the Strikers easily handled the [[Miami Hurricanes]] and the junior side, [[Calry Bohemian FC]], of [[Sligo]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Smith|first=Mike|url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/301850350/?terms=Strikers|title=The U-M athletic team nobody knows|date=April 15, 1980|work=Miami News|page=1C|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Wieczorek|first=Dave|url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/234942061/?terms=Strikers|title=Dutchman Pot prefers Strikers guard duty|date=April 17, 1980|work=Fort Lauderdale News|page=3D|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref> They later fell to visiting [[Sunderland A.F.C.]] in a midseason friendly in May.\n\n==== Results summaries ====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%; text-align:center\"\n!Date!!Opponent!!Venue!!Result!!Attendance!!Scorers\n|- bgcolor=\"#ffdddd\"\n|{{left}}March 2, 1980\n|{{left}}[[FIU Panthers men's soccer|FIU Sunblazers]]\n|[[Florida International University|FIU South Campus]]\n|2\u20133\n|\n|<small>???, ???</small>\n|-\n|- bgcolor=\"ddffdd\"\n|{{left}}March 9, 1980\n|{{left}}[[Miami Dade College|Miami Dade North Falcons]]\n|[[MDC North Campus|Dade North Stadium]]\n|8\u20130\n| \n|<small>M\u00fcller (3), Bonvallet (3), Cubillas, Cacciatore </small>\n|-\n|- bgcolor=\"ffdddd\"\n|{{left}}March 12, 1980\n|{{left}}[[Detroit Express]]\n|[[John I. Leonard Community High School|Leonard High School]]\n|0\u20131\n|\n|\n|-\n|- bgcolor=\"ffdddd\"\n|{{left}}March 16, 1980\n|{{left}}[[Detroit Express]]\n|[[Bryant Stadium]]\n|1\u20132''<small>(SO)</small>''\n|\n|<small>Nico Bodonczy</small>\n|-\n|- bgcolor=\"ffdddd\"\n|{{left}}March 19, 1980\n|{{left}}[[Minnesota Kicks]]\n|[[Coral Springs High School]]\n|0\u20131\n|\n|\n|-\n|- bgcolor= \n|{{left}}March 21, 1980\n|{{left}}[[Atlanta Chiefs]]\n|[[Lockhart Stadium]]\n| '''\u2013'''\n| '''\u2013'''\n|'''MATCH CANCELED'''\n|-\n|- bgcolor= \"ffebad\"\n|{{left}}March 22, 1980\n|{{left}}{{flagicon|PER}} [[Alianza Lima]]\n|[[Estadio Alejandro Villanueva|Estadio Alianza]]\n|1\u20131\n|35,000\n|<small> David Irving </small>\n|-\n|- bgcolor= \"ffebad\"\n|{{left}}March 24, 1980\n|{{left}}{{flagicon|PER}} [[Club Universitario de Deportes|Club Universitario]]\n|[[Estadio Alejandro Villanueva|Estadio Alianza]]\n|1\u20131\n|35,000\n|<small> Gerd M\u00fcller </small>\n|- bgcolor=\"ddffdd\"\n|{{left}}April 14, 1980\n|{{left}}[[Miami Hurricanes]]\n|[[Mark Light Stadium]]\n|6\u20131\n| \n|<small>David Irving </small>\n|- bgcolor=\"ddffdd\"\n|{{left}}April 16, 1980\n|{{left}}{{flagicon|IRE}} [[Calry Bohemian FC]]\n|Strikers practice facility\n|8\u20130\n| \n|<small>David Irving (3), Nico Bodonczy (2), Mike Ortiz-Velez (2)</small>\n|-\n|- bgcolor=\"ffdddd\"\n|{{left}}May 14, 1980\n|{{left}}{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Sunderland A.F.C.]]\n|[[Lockhart Stadium]]\n|1\u20132\n| 4,649<ref>https://www.newspapers.com/image/134924661/?terms=Sunderland</ref>\n|<small>Ray Hudson (pk)</small>\n|-\n|}\n\n=== NASL regular season ===\n\n==== Results summaries ====\n{{Empty section|date=November 2013}}\n\n==== Results by round ====\n{{Empty section|date=November 2013}}\n\n==== Match reports ====\n{{Empty section|date=November 2013}}\n\n=== NASL Playoffs ===\n\n'''Playoffs'''\n''In 1979 and 1980, if a playoff series was tied at one victory each, a full 30 minute mini-game was played. If neither team held an advantage after the 30 minutes, the teams would then move on to a shoot-out to determine a series winner.''<ref>https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=0rg0AAAAIBAJ&sjid=B24FAAAAIBAJ&pg=4566,2362302&dq=nasl+record+shootout&hl=en</ref>{{-}}\n\n==== First round====\n{| style=border-collapse:collapse border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=2\n|- align=center bgcolor=#efefef\n!width=180|Lower seed\n!width=5|\n!width=180|Higher seed\n!width=80|Game 1\n!width=80|Game 2\n!width=100|Mini-game\n|width=260|\n|- align=center bgcolor=fffafa\n|align=right|[[California Surf]]|| - ||align=left|'''Fort Lauderdale Strikers'''|| 1\u20132 || 2\u20130 || 0\u20131 <small>''(SO, 2\u20133)''</small> || <small>August 28 \u2022 [[Anaheim Stadium]] \u2022 2,929<br>August 31 \u2022 [[Lockhart Stadium]] \u2022 15,282</small>\n|}{{-}}\n\n=